TPRS Poisson Regression with changing confounders

Samuel Herold, Kayleigh Keller

This simulation looks at the effectiveness of varying degrees of freedom (up to 100) of Thin Plate Regression Splines as basis functions in a Poisson Regression to try to remove spatial confounding. The confounding surface is recreated at the start of every loop/sample of the simulation. The true b1 is 1, and is our target. Samples of size 1000 were taken 50 times. Two situations were examined: g = .1/c = .25 and g = .25/c = .25.
